This article is a transcript of remarks made by Governor Abbott and President Trump during a visit to the Texas Department of Public Safety Emergency Operations Center in Austin. Governor Abbott expressed gratitude for the President's support and assistance in responding to the catastrophic storm and flooding caused by Hurricane Harvey. President Trump acknowledged the long-term and historic nature of the disaster and pledged to work with Congress to provide necessary resources for recovery efforts. Various officials, including Secretary Price, Administrator McMahon, and Secretary Carson, also discussed the efforts being made by their respective departments to provide medical care, financial assistance, and housing support to those affected by the hurricane. The President emphasized the importance of coordination and cooperation among different agencies in order to effectively respond to and recover from the disaster.